{"name": "Cauterize", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-hand-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You reach out and sear a creature&rsquo;s open wounds. The creature takes 2d6 fire damage and must make a Dexterity (Save) Check to try and pull away, which it can choose to fail. On a failed save, you choose one of the following to happen:</p><ul><li>All of the creature&rsquo;s stacks of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;are removed, and it suffers an additional 1d6 fire damage for each stack removed.</li><li>The creature resists the spell&rsquo;s fire damage and gains temporary hit points equal to the fire damage taken. This damage cannot reduce a creature below 1 hit point. Additionally, all of the creature&rsquo;s stacks of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;are removed, gaining an additional 1d6 temporary hit points per removed stack.</li></ul><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>2 Mana: After resolving the spell&rsquo;s effects, re-apply half of the stacks of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;the spell removed.</li><li>X Mana: For each extra Mana you spend, up to your charge limit, you can also remove one stack of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;from yourself. If the target fails its save, you can include these in the total stacks of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;removed when determining the spell&rsquo;s effects on the target.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "evo", "components": {"somatic": true, "verbal": true, "material": true, "ritual": false, "concentration": false}, "materials": {"value": "A bandage and a dab of oil", "consumed": false, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "save", "activation": {"type": "action", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": "inst"}, "range": {"value": "0", "long": null, "units": "touch"}, "target": {"value": "1", "width": null, "units": "", "type": "creature"}, "damage": {"parts": [["2d6", "fire"]], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "dex", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "WR681XHI4K1RFFID", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Corporeal Semblance", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/magic/control/energy-stream-link-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You temporarily change the race of one willing creature you touch, giving them the form, appearance, and racial abilities of a creature from a different lineage. For the duration, the target replaces all of their racial abilities with those of the creature that the spell&rsquo;s material components were taken from, ignoring any changes to attributes, maximum hit points, lifespan, proficiencies, languages, or equipment.&nbsp;</p><p>The target&rsquo;s new form loosely resembles that of the copied creature such that they could be mistaken for a relative, but not to the extent that anyone would confuse the two. Within these constraints, the target can fine-tune aspects of their new appearance, such as hairstyle, body markings, age, and body shape, as long as they are possible for the new race and relatively similar to the copied creature.</p><p>The magic of the spell provides the target with a basic understanding of their new form&rsquo;s capabilities and helps acclimate them to any unusual externalities such as new senses, different forms of locomotion, or an alien set of vocal cords.</p><p>This spell struggles to perfectly recreate any magical aspects the target&rsquo;s new form may have. Abilities that would restore a creature&rsquo;s mana can only restore up to 1 mana total across the transformation&rsquo;s duration. Additionally, the target must use its own mana to cast any spells of 2nd level or higher granted by their new race, even if they would normally be able to cast them without mana.</p><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>0 Mana: The spell no longer requires Concentration but only lasts 1 hour.</li><li>1 Mana: The target&rsquo;s clothing and armor alter and resize to accommodate their new form, but the material and style remains the same. They remain in this altered state for the spell&rsquo;s duration, even when doffed.</li><li>2 Mana: The spell consumes an additional valid material component, taken from a different creature. The target gains the core race abilities from one and the branch race abilities from the other, and their new form resembles a hybrid of the two.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "tra", "components": {"somatic": true, "verbal": false, "material": true, "ritual": false, "concentration": true}, "materials": {"value": "A lock of hair, vial of blood, or other fragment taken from a societal creature in its natural form, which the spell consumes", "consumed": true, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "util", "activation": {"type": "minute", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "8", "units": "hour"}, "range": {"value": "0", "long": null, "units": "touch"}, "target": {"value": "1", "width": null, "units": "", "type": "creature"}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "9J6AS3OK4M7GS3NW", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Corrosive Wash", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/magic/acid/dissolve-bone-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You conjure a shower of corrosive acid upon a target within range. The target must make a Dexterity (Save) check. On a failed save, it takes 2d10 acid damage and becomes coated in bubbling acid, temporarily weakening its defenses. If the creature is benefiting from natural armor, medium armor, heavy armor, or a shield then it suffers a -2 penalty to AC until the end of your next turn. This reduction to AC cannot be combined with other effects that reduce AC, such as multiple castings of this spell.</p><p>On a successful save, the creature takes half of the damage and suffers no other effects.</p><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: The AC reduction applies to any target that fails their save, regardless of what armor or shields they have.</li><li>2 Mana: The AC penalty increases to -3.</li><li>2 Mana: In addition to targeting a creature, you can cause the acid to permanently eat holes in one Large or smaller object not being worn or carried or one 5-foot section of wall that is within 5 feet of the target. As well as weakening the structural integrity of the object or surface, any creature that attempts to use it as cover gains one tier lower of obstruction from the object than it normally would. For example, a creature fully obscured by it would only gain the benefits of three-quarters cover. Weapons affected by this deal a damage die size smaller.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "con", "components": {"somatic": true, "verbal": true, "material": true, "ritual": false, "concentration": false}, "materials": {"value": "vinegar, a piece of limestone", "consumed": false, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "save", "activation": {"type": "action", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "1", "units": "round"}, "range": {"value": "30", "long": null, "units": "ft"}, "target": {"value": "1", "width": null, "units": "", "type": "creature"}, "damage": {"parts": [["2d10", "acid"]], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "dex", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "DV87F1MQUC5C59VW", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Escape", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/creatures/birds/birds-flock-fly-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>With a startling shout, you momentarily transform into a harmless flying cloud of vapor, beasts, or spirits. While transformed in this way, your size becomes Tiny, you have the ability to fly, and you gain an additional 30 ft of movement this turn.&nbsp;</p><p>You revert to your normal form once you have moved 30 ft, you attempt to take any other actions, or you end your turn. If you revert in a space too small to contain you, you take 5 force damage and are forced back along the path you took until there is enough space to accommodate you.</p><p>When you transform, all equipment you are wearing or carrying transforms with you, and you automatically escape any @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled}&nbsp;or @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.1EK5V6KTYAWC6S69]{Restrained}&nbsp;conditions caused by non-magical sources. Magical effects causing you to be @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled}&nbsp;or @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.1EK5V6KTYAWC6S69]{Restrained}&nbsp;are only suppressed while you are transformed.</p><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: If used as a Desperate Action, you gain advantage on Dexterity (Save) Checks and an additional +2 AC until the end of the interrupted creature&rsquo;s turn.</li><li>2 Mana: One willing creature within 5ft of you is also transformed and carried with you. When your transformation ends they are deposited in the nearest empty space.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "tra", "components": {"somatic": false, "verbal": true, "material": false, "ritual": false, "concentration": false}, "materials": {"value": "", "consumed": false, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "util", "activation": {"type": "minor", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "1", "units": "round"}, "range": {"value": "0", "long": null, "units": "self"}, "target": {"value": "1", "width": null, "units": "", "type": "creature"}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "2PJ8ZPXCT48NTRUF", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Ophidian Kiss", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/serpent-horned-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your teeth grow into vicious fangs, dripping with deadly venom. Make a melee spell attack against a creature within 5 feet. On a hit, the creature takes 2d6 poison damage and gains the @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;condition. Hitting a creature that is already at the maximum stacks of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;inflicts one level of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion}&nbsp;until the bleeding is cured, as long as it was not already suffering from @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion}&nbsp;resulting from this spell.&nbsp;</p><p>For the spell&rsquo;s duration, you can repeat the spell attack against any creature within 5 feet as an action.</p><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: Until the spell ends, you can repeat the spell attack in place of a weapon attack when a creature provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you.</li><li>2 Mana: The poison damage increases by 1d6.</li><li>3 Mana: Creatures afflicted with @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;from this spell are also @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9X088PM7H5U2S1HQ]{Sickened}&nbsp;until the @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}&nbsp;is cured.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "tra", "components": {"somatic": true, "verbal": true, "material": true, "ritual": false, "concentration": true}, "materials": {"value": "the fang of a snake", "consumed": false, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "msak", "activation": {"type": "action", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "1", "units": "minute"}, "range": {"value": "0", "long": null, "units": "self"}, "target": {"value": "1", "width": null, "units": "", "type": "creature"}, "damage": {"parts": [["2d6", "poison"]], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "IGNXR8HBQZS1JVCY", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Snowslide", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/magic/water/ice-snowman.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>A cascade of snow and ice sweeps through a 20-foot cube centered on a point you choose within range. When you cast this spell, choose one side of the cube (excluding the top and bottom) to be the side of egress. Each creature within the cube must make a Constitution (Save) Check. On a failed save, a creature takes 3d8 cold damage and is moved directly towards the chosen egress side until it is ejected from the cube or is stopped by an obstacle. On a successful save, a creature takes half damage and is not moved. Afterwards, the snow rapidly melts and dissipates, leaving behind only small clumps and puddles.</p><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: Snow coats the ground in the cube for the next minute. While snow-covered, the area is considered difficult terrain. The snow within each 5-foot space melts early when it or a creature in it is subjected to any fire damage.</li><li>2 Mana: The size increases to a 30-foot cube.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "con", "components": {"somatic": true, "verbal": true, "material": true, "ritual": false, "concentration": false}, "materials": {"value": "A bottle of mountain springwater", "consumed": false, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "save", "activation": {"type": "action", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": "inst"}, "range": {"value": "60", "long": null, "units": "ft"}, "target": {"value": "20", "width": null, "units": "ft", "type": "cube"}, "damage": {"parts": [["3d8", "cold"]], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "con", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "HVOF7QNI17K2O6C1", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Static Spark", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/magic/lightning/projectile-tendrils-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You hurl a ball of electricity at a creature within range, making a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 2d10 lightning damage and becomes charged with static electricity. On a miss, the spell ends. For the duration, you can use your action to make a ranged spell attack against any other creature within 15 feet of the charged creature, dealing 2d6 lightning damage on a hit.</p><p>Charge: This is a spell that can be Charged, modifying its effects. Costs and effects are as follow:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: If you miss the initial spell attack, the spell does not end and the target creature&rsquo;s space becomes charged with electricity instead. The rest of the spell functions as normal but with the words &ldquo;charged creature&rdquo; replaced with &ldquo;charged space&rdquo;.</li><li>1 Mana: Instead of making a spell attack, you can touch a willing creature to harmlessly charge them with electricity instead. The spell functions as normal, skipping the initial attack damage.</li><li>4 Mana: The subsequent spell attacks can be triggered as a minor action.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "level": "2", "charge": true, "school": "evo", "components": {"somatic": true, "verbal": true, "material": true, "ritual": false, "concentration": true}, "materials": {"value": "A piece of fur and a glass sphere", "consumed": false, "cost": "", "supply": 0}, "attribute": "spell", "actionType": "rsak", "activation": {"type": "action", "cost": "1", "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "1", "units": "minute"}, "range": {"value": "60", "long": null, "units": "ft"}, "target": {"value": "1", "width": null, "units": "", "type": "creature"}, "damage": {"parts": [["2d10", "lightning"], ["2d6", "lightning"]], "versatile": ""}, "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "showInAttacks": false}, "_id": "BNG42U9X3RWWFWXA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
